###########################################################################
#  box_save_restore - the smallest reproducer for the gsave/grestore       #
#  path-save round trip exercised by issue #208.  Inside a raw @Graphic    #
#  we call LoutBox (which deposits the @Box path on the current path),    #
#  gsave, fill the path with a light grey, grestore, then stroke the      #
#  same path with the default 1pt black.  The result is a filled box      #
#  with a sharp black border.                                              #
#                                                                          #
#  If z53.c drops the path across the gsave/grestore boundary (the bug    #
#  tracked in #208) the stroke after grestore lands on an empty path and  #
#  the border disappears in the SVG render while staying intact in the    #
#  PS reference -- so any regression of that path-save behaviour flips    #
#  this snippet's verdict.                                                 #
###########################################################################

@SysInclude { doc }
@Doc @Text @Begin
@PP
Filled box with black border via gsave / fill / grestore / stroke:
@DP
@CentredDisplay {
   "newpath LoutBox"
   "gsave 0.85 setgray fill grestore"
   "0 setgray 1 setlinewidth stroke"
} @Graphic { 4c @Wide 2.5c @High }
@End @Text
